5000|$|The Annunciation {{shows the}} {{archangel}} Gabriel entering {{the house of}} the Virgin Mary to tell her that she will soon bear the child Jesus, whose name means [...] "savior". Gabriel holds an olive branch in his hand, a traditional symbol of peace, while pointing at the <b>Holy</b> <b>Ghost's</b> dove with the other. The dove is descending from heaven, {{from the center of the}} mandorla of eight angels above, about to enter the Virgin's right ear. In fact, along the path of the dove, viewers see Gabriel's utterance: [...] ("Hail, full of grace, the Lord is with thee."). The angel's mantle shows a detailed [...] "tartar cloth" [...] pattern and fine gilt feathers.|$|R
